- <i>Hola.</i>

415
00:23:50.660 --> 00:23:52.090
<font color="#138ce9">MIGUEL:</font> <i>Tia</i> Victoria?

416
00:23:52.090 --> 00:23:54.590
He doesn't
seem entirely dead.

417
00:23:54.590 --> 00:23:57.500
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTS)</font>
- He's not quite alive either.

418
00:23:57.500 --> 00:24:00.100
We need <i>Mama</i> Imelda.
She'll know how to fix this.

419
00:24:00.100 --> 00:24:04.100
<i>Oye!</i> It's <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

420
00:24:04.100 --> 00:24:05.500
- She couldn't cross over.
- <font color="#ff00ff">(ALL GASP)</font>

421
00:24:05.510 --> 00:24:07.940
- She's stuck!
- On the other side!

422
00:24:07.940 --> 00:24:10.740
<i>Tio</i> Oscar? <i>Tio</i> Felipe?

423
00:24:10.740 --> 00:24:12.840
- Oh. Hey. Miguel.
- <font color="#ff00ff">(BOTH GASP)</font>

424
00:24:12.840 --> 00:24:15.480
I have a feeling this has
something to do with you.

425
00:24:15.480 --> 00:24:17.610
But if <i>Mama</i> Imelda
can't come to us...

426
00:24:17.620 --> 00:24:19.880
Then we are going to her.
<i>Vamonos!</i>

427
00:24:19.890 --> 00:24:22.070
<font color="#ff00ff">(DANTE BARKING)</font>

428
00:24:23.790 --> 00:24:25.110
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

429
00:24:33.800 --> 00:24:35.170
Whoa.

430
00:24:35.170 --> 00:24:37.920
Come on. Miguel.
It's okay.

431
00:24:39.610 --> 00:24:41.060
<font color="#ff00ff">(DANTE BARKS)</font>

432
00:24:48.480 --> 00:24:50.620
<font color="#ff00ff">(DANTE CONTINUES BARKING)</font>

433
00:24:50.620 --> 00:24:55.100
Dante? Dante!
Dante. wait up!

434
00:24:57.530 --> 00:25:02.380
You got to stay with me. boy.
We don't know... where...

435
00:25:22.790 --> 00:25:26.220
This isn't a dream then.
You're all really out there.

436
00:25:26.220 --> 00:25:28.190
- You thought we weren't?
- Well. I don't know.

437
00:25:28.190 --> 00:25:30.060
I thought it might've been
one of those

438
00:25:30.060 --> 00:25:31.990
made up things
that adults tell kids.

439
00:25:31.990 --> 00:25:33.560
Like vitamins.

440
00:25:33.560 --> 00:25:35.700
Miguel.
vitamins are a real thing.

441
00:25:35.700 --> 00:25:37.870
Well. now I'm thinking
maybe they could be.

442
00:25:37.870 --> 00:25:39.930
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>
- <i>Mija.</i> it's not nice to stare at...

443
00:25:39.940 --> 00:25:41.600
<i>Ay!</i> Santa Maria!

444
00:25:41.610 --> 00:25:43.020
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHOOSHING)</font>

445
00:25:49.280 --> 00:25:53.680
Are those...
Alebrijes! But those are...

446
00:25:53.690 --> 00:25:56.220
<font color="#138ce9">OSCAR:</font> Real alebrijes.
Spirit creatures.

447
00:25:56.220 --> 00:25:58.090
They guide souls
on their journey.

448
00:25:58.090 --> 00:26:00.560
Watch your step. They
make <i>caquitas</i> everywhere.

449
00:26:00.560 --> 00:26:02.760
<font color="#138ce9">ANNOUNCER:</font> <i>Welcome back
to the Land of the Dead.</i>

450
00:26:02.760 --> 00:26:05.600
<i>Please have all offerings
ready for re-entry.</i>

451
00:26:05.600 --> 00:26:07.830
Welcome back.
Anything to declare?

452
00:26:07.830 --> 00:26:09.300
Some churros.
From my family.

453
00:26:09.300 --> 00:26:11.300
<font color="#138ce9">ARRIVALS AGENT:</font> How wonderful. Next.

454
00:26:11.300 --> 00:26:13.170
<font color="#138ce9">ANNOUNCER:</font> <i>If you are
experiencing travel issues.</i>

455
00:26:13.170 --> 00:26:14.900
<i>agents at
the Department of Family...</i>

456
00:26:14.910 --> 00:26:17.140
<i>Reunions are
available to assist you.</i>

457
00:26:17.140 --> 00:26:18.930
<font color="#138ce9">DEPARTURES AGENT:</font> Next family. please.

458
00:26:21.310 --> 00:26:22.410
<font color="#ff00ff">(DINGS)</font>

459
00:26:22.420 --> 00:26:24.980
Oh! Your photos
are on your son's <i>ofrenda.</i>

460
00:26:24.980 --> 00:26:26.350
Have a great visit.

461
00:26:26.350 --> 00:26:27.620
<font color="#138ce9">BOTH:</font> <i>Gracias.</i>

462
00:26:27.620 --> 00:26:29.650
<font color="#138ce9">ANNOUNCER:</font> <i>And remember
to return before sunrise.</i>

463
00:26:29.660 --> 00:26:30.860
<i>Enjoy your visit.</i>

464
00:26:30.860 --> 00:26:33.190
- Next.
- <font color="#ff00ff">(DINGS)</font>

465
00:26:33.190 --> 00:26:36.730
Your photo's on your dentist's <i>ofrenda.</i>
Enjoy your visit.

466
00:26:36.730 --> 00:26:38.510
- <i>Gracias.</i>
- Next?

467
00:26:40.800 --> 00:26:43.030
Yes! It is I.
Frida Kahlo.

468
00:26:43.040 --> 00:26:44.600
Shall we skip
the scanner?

469
00:26:44.600 --> 00:26:48.320
I'm on so many <i>ofrendas</i> it'll just
overwhelm your blinky thingy.

470
00:26:48.880 --> 00:26:50.040
<font color="#ff00ff">(BUZZING)</font>

471
00:26:50.040 --> 00:26:54.610
Well. shoot. looks like no one
put up your photo. Frida.

472
00:26:54.620 --> 00:26:58.880
Okay. when I said I was Frida.
just now. that was a lie.

473
00:26:58.890 --> 00:27:00.280
And I apologize
for doing that.

474
00:27:00.290 --> 00:27:03.160
No photo on an <i>ofrenda.</i>
no crossing the bridge.

475
00:27:03.160 --> 00:27:06.940
I'm just gonna zip right over.
You won't even know I'm gone.

476
00:27:07.900 --> 00:27:10.080
- Hey!
- <font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHS)</font>

477
00:27:10.700 --> 00:27:12.010
<font color="#ff00ff">(WOMAN YELPS)</font>

478
00:27:12.900 --> 00:27:14.510
<font color="#ff00ff">(PANTING)</font>

479
00:27:15.640 --> 00:27:19.370
Almost... there.
Just a little further.

480
00:27:19.370 --> 00:27:21.220
<font color="#ff00ff">(PANTING)</font>

481
00:27:22.240 --> 00:27:23.630
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

482
00:27:24.180 --> 00:27:25.240
Upsy-daisy...

483
00:27:25.250 --> 00:27:29.650
Fine. Okay. Fine. who cares?
Dumb flower bridge!

484
00:27:29.650 --> 00:27:33.750
Aw. I don't know what I'd do
if no one put up my photo.

485
00:27:33.760 --> 00:27:36.060
- <font color="#138ce9">ARRIVALS AGENT:</font> Next?
- Oh! Come. <i>mijo.</i> It's our turn.

486
00:27:36.060 --> 00:27:38.990
Welcome back. <i>amigos.</i>
Anything to declare?

487
00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:42.410
As a matter of fact. yes.
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)</font>

488
00:27:42.800 --> 00:27:44.110
<i>Hola.</i>

489
00:27:50.940 --> 00:27:53.110
<font color="#138ce9">MALE ANNOUNCER:</font> <i>Paging Marta Gonzales-Ramos.</i>

490
00:27:53.110 --> 00:27:55.990
<i>Please report to Level Seven.</i>

491
00:28:00.280 --> 00:28:02.030
<font color="#138ce9">MIGUEL:</font> Whoa!

492
00:28:02.380 --> 00:28:03.700
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL GASP)</font>

493
00:28:05.220 --> 00:28:07.270
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font> I miss my nose.

494
00:28:12.400 --> 00:28:14.550
<font color="#ff00ff">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)</font>

495
00:28:16.300 --> 00:28:18.270
Come on. help us out. <i>amigo.</i>

496
00:28:18.270 --> 00:28:19.740
We got to get to
a dozen <i>ofrendas</i> tonight.

497
00:28:19.740 --> 00:28:23.870
We are not visiting your ex-wife's
family for <i>Dia de Muertos!</i>

498
00:28:23.870 --> 00:28:26.410
I demand to speak
to the person in charge!

499
00:28:26.410 --> 00:28:29.310
I'm sorry. <i>senora.</i> it says
here no one put up your photo.

500
00:28:29.310 --> 00:28:33.880
My family always puts my
photo on the <i>ofrenda.</i>

501
00:28:33.880 --> 00:28:36.990
That devil box tells
you nothing but lies!

502
00:28:36.990 --> 00:28:41.760
- <i>Mama</i> Imelda? <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>
- Oh. <i>mi familia!</i>

503
00:28:41.760 --> 00:28:43.360
They wouldn't let me
cross the bridge.

504
00:28:43.360 --> 00:28:45.860
Tell this woman
and her devil box

505
00:28:45.860 --> 00:28:48.400
that my photo
is on the <i>ofrenda.</i>

506
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:51.870
<font color="#ff00ff">(STAMMERS)</font> Well. we never
made it to the <i>ofrenda.</i>

507
00:28:51.870 --> 00:28:55.590
- What?
- We ran into... <font color="#ff00ff">(STAMMERS)</font>

508
00:28:58.280 --> 00:29:01.390
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font> Miguel?
- <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

509
00:29:01.810 --> 00:29:04.150
What is going on?

510
00:29:04.150 --> 00:29:06.450
You the Rivera family?

511
00:29:06.450 --> 00:29:08.050
<font color="#ff00ff">(COMPUTER EXPLODES)</font>

512
00:29:08.060 --> 00:29:09.420
Well. you're cursed.

513
00:29:09.420 --> 00:29:10.560
- <font color="#ff00ff">(ALL GASP)</font>
- What?

514
00:29:10.560 --> 00:29:13.190
<i>Dia de los Muertos</i> is the
night to give to the dead.

515
00:29:13.190 --> 00:29:14.790
You stole from the dead!

516
00:29:14.790 --> 00:29:16.160
But I wasn't
stealing the guitar.

517
00:29:16.160 --> 00:29:17.290
Guitar?

518
00:29:17.300 --> 00:29:18.900
It was my
great-great-grandfather's.

519
00:29:18.900 --> 00:29:20.200
He would have
wanted me to have it.

520
00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:23.330
Ah. ah. ah. We do not speak
of that musician.

521
00:29:23.340 --> 00:29:25.070
He is dead to this family.

522
00:29:25.070 --> 00:29:27.040
<font color="#138ce9">MIGUEL:</font> Uh.
you're all dead.

523
00:29:27.040 --> 00:29:28.110
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNEEZES)</font>

524
00:29:28.110 --> 00:29:30.780
I am sorry.
Whose alebrije is that?

525
00:29:30.780 --> 00:29:32.040
That's just Dante.

526
00:29:32.050 --> 00:29:34.180
He sure doesn't
look like an alebrije.

527
00:29:34.180 --> 00:29:35.780
He just looks
like a plain old dog.

528
00:29:35.780 --> 00:29:38.050
Or a sausage someone dropped
in a barbershop.

529
00:29:38.050 --> 00:29:41.820
Whatever he is. I am
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNEEZES)</font> terribly allergic.

530
00:29:41.820 --> 00:29:43.490
But Dante
doesn't have any hair.

531
00:29:43.490 --> 00:29:46.190
And I don't have a nose.
and yet. here we are.

532
00:29:46.190 --> 00:29:47.390
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNEEZES)</font>

533
00:29:47.400 --> 00:29:51.100
But none of this explains
why I couldn't cross over.

534
00:29:51.100 --> 00:29:52.780
Oh! <font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)</font>

535
00:29:53.070 --> 00:29:54.230
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL GASP)</font>

536
00:29:54.240 --> 00:29:56.970
You took my photo
off the <i>ofrenda?</i>

537
00:29:56.970 --> 00:29:59.070
- It was an accident!
- How do we send him back?

538
00:29:59.070 --> 00:30:01.810
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)</font> Well.
since it's a family matter...

539
00:30:01.810 --> 00:30:04.240
the way to undo
a family curse

540
00:30:04.250 --> 00:30:06.980
- is to get your family's blessing.
- That's it?

541
00:30:06.980 --> 00:30:08.380
Get your family's blessing

542
00:30:08.380 --> 00:30:10.980
and everything should
go back to normal.

543
00:30:10.990 --> 00:30:13.020
But you got
to do it by sunrise.

544
00:30:13.020 --> 00:30:14.950
<font color="#ff00ff">(STAMMERS)</font>
What happens at sunrise?

545
00:30:14.960 --> 00:30:16.810
<i>Hijole!</i> Your hand!

546
00:30:17.430 --> 00:30:18.740
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

547
00:30:20.960 --> 00:30:21.960
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

548
00:30:21.970 --> 00:30:24.830
Whoa. Miguel. can't have
you fainting on us.

549
00:30:24.830 --> 00:30:27.400
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font> But not to worry.
Your family's here.

550
00:30:27.400 --> 00:30:29.440
You can get
your blessing right now.

551
00:30:29.440 --> 00:30:34.410
<i>Cempasuchil. cempasuchil.</i>
Aha! <i>Perdon. senora.</i>

552
00:30:34.410 --> 00:30:35.380
Oh. <font color="#ff00ff">(GIGGLES)</font>

553
00:30:35.380 --> 00:30:38.300
Now. you look at the living
and say his name.

554
00:30:39.180 --> 00:30:40.210
Miguel.

555
00:30:40.220 --> 00:30:43.520
Nailed it. Now say.
"I give you my blessing."

556
00:30:43.520 --> 00:30:45.570
I give you my blessing.

557
00:30:47.990 --> 00:30:51.390
I give you my blessing
to go home...

558
00:30:51.390 --> 00:30:54.560
to put my photo
back on the <i>ofrenda.</i>

559
00:30:54.570 --> 00:30:57.000
and to never
play music again.

560
00:30:57.000 --> 00:30:58.870
What? She can't do that!

561
00:30:58.870 --> 00:31:02.140
Well. technically. she can
add any condition she wants.

562
00:31:02.140 --> 00:31:04.270
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font> Fine.

563
00:31:04.280 --> 00:31:06.490
<font color="#138ce9">CLERK:</font> Then you hand
the petal to Miguel.

564
00:31:12.280 --> 00:31:14.150
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

565
00:31:14.150 --> 00:31:15.600
<font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHS IN RELIEF)</font>

566
00:31:19.020 --> 00:31:20.370
No skeletons!

567
00:31:20.930 --> 00:31:22.470
<font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHS)</font>

568
00:31:24.460 --> 00:31:26.740
Mariachi Plaza.
here I come.

569
00:31:27.900 --> 00:31:29.480
<font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTS)</font>

570
00:31:30.970 --> 00:31:33.170
Two seconds and you already
break your promise.

571
00:31:33.170 --> 00:31:37.040
This isn't fair. It's my life.
You already had yours.

572
00:31:37.040 --> 00:31:39.110
<i>Papa</i> Julio.
I ask for your blessing.

573
00:31:39.110 --> 00:31:42.210
- <font color="#ff00ff">(WHIMPERS)</font>
- <i>Tia</i> Rosita? Oscar?

574
00:31:42.220 --> 00:31:45.080
- <font color="#ff00ff">(ALL WHIMPERING)</font>
- Felipe? <i>Tia</i> Victoria?

575
00:31:45.080 --> 00:31:49.490
Don't make this hard. <i>mijo.</i>
You go home my way or no way.

576
00:31:49.490 --> 00:31:51.350
You really hate
music that much?

577
00:31:51.360 --> 00:31:54.510
I will not let you go down
the same path he did.

578
00:31:56.930 --> 00:32:01.130
The same path he did.
He's family.

579
00:32:01.130 --> 00:32:02.940
Listen to your <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

580
00:32:02.940 --> 00:32:04.200
She's just
looking out for you.

581
00:32:04.200 --> 00:32:05.270
Be reasonable.

582
00:32:05.270 --> 00:32:08.610
<i>Con permiso.</i>
I need to visit the restroom.

583
00:32:08.610 --> 00:32:10.390
Be right back.

584
00:32:11.250 --> 00:32:13.340
Uh. should we tell him
there are no restrooms

585
00:32:13.350 --> 00:32:14.660
in the Land of the Dead?

586
00:32:15.250 --> 00:32:16.830
<font color="#ff00ff">(PANTING)</font>

587
00:32:23.260 --> 00:32:24.670
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

588
00:32:27.700 --> 00:32:28.860
<i>Vamonos.</i>

589
00:32:28.860 --> 00:32:31.560
<font color="#138ce9">PATROLWOMAN:</font> We got a family
looking for a living boy.

590
00:32:31.570 --> 00:32:34.300
If I want to be a musician.
I need a musician's blessing.

591
00:32:34.300 --> 00:32:36.370
We got to find
my great-great-grandpa.

592
00:32:36.370 --> 00:32:38.420
- Hold it. <i>muchacho.</i>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

593
00:32:40.440 --> 00:32:42.010
<font color="#ff00ff">(SHOUTS)</font>

594
00:32:42.010 --> 00:32:43.380
I found that living boy!

595
00:32:43.380 --> 00:32:45.610
Oh. whoa. excuse me.
Excuse me. folks.

596
00:32:45.610 --> 00:32:46.960
Excuse me.

597
00:32:47.720 --> 00:32:49.230
Oh.

598
00:32:52.990 --> 00:32:55.260
No. no. Dante!

599
00:32:55.260 --> 00:32:58.290
Disturbing the peace.
Fleeing an officer.

600
00:32:58.290 --> 00:33:00.160
Falsifying a unibrow.

601
00:33:00.160 --> 00:33:02.430
- That's illegal?
- Very illegal.

602
00:33:02.430 --> 00:33:04.530
You need to clean up
your act. <i>amigo.</i>

603
00:33:04.530 --> 00:33:08.270
<i>Amigo?</i> Oh. that's so nice
to hear you say that

604
00:33:08.270 --> 00:33:10.070
because I have just had a...

605
00:33:10.070 --> 00:33:13.010
really hard <i>Dia de Muertos</i>
and I could really use

606
00:33:13.010 --> 00:33:14.010
- an <i>amigo</i> right now.
- <font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

607
00:33:14.010 --> 00:33:16.740
And <i>amigos.</i>
they help their <i>amigos.</i>

608
00:33:16.750 --> 00:33:19.450
You get me across
that bridge tonight.

609
00:33:19.450 --> 00:33:21.050
and I'll make it
worth your while.

610
00:33:21.050 --> 00:33:24.150
Oh! You like de la Cruz?
He and I go way back.

611
00:33:24.160 --> 00:33:27.490
I can get you front row seats to
his Sunrise Spectacular show.

612
00:33:27.490 --> 00:33:29.690
I'll get you backstage.
You can meet him.

613
00:33:29.690 --> 00:33:31.430
You just got to let me
cross that bridge!

614
00:33:31.430 --> 00:33:33.600
I should lock you up
for the rest of the holiday.

615
00:33:33.600 --> 00:33:37.700
But my shift's almost up and I
want to visit my living family.

616
00:33:37.700 --> 00:33:40.420
So I'm letting you off
with a warning.

617
00:33:41.370 --> 00:33:43.510
Can I at least
get my costume back?

618
00:33:43.510 --> 00:33:45.310
Uh... No.

619
00:33:45.310 --> 00:33:47.790
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font> Some <i>amigo.</i>

620
00:33:50.250 --> 00:33:53.720
Hey! Hey!
You really know de la Cruz?

621
00:33:53.720 --> 00:33:56.350
Who wants to... Ahh!
<i>Ay!</i> You're alive!

622
00:33:56.350 --> 00:33:58.060
Shh! Yeah. I'm alive.

623
00:33:58.060 --> 00:34:00.120
And if I want to get back
to the Land of the Living...

624
00:34:00.120 --> 00:34:01.590
I need de la Cruz's blessing.

625
00:34:01.590 --> 00:34:03.190
That's weirdly specific.

626
00:34:03.200 --> 00:34:04.730
He's my
great-great-grandfather.

627
00:34:04.730 --> 00:34:07.310
<font color="#ff00ff">(STAMMERING)</font>
He's your Gr... What?

628
00:34:07.730 --> 00:34:09.670
Ugh.

629
00:34:09.670 --> 00:34:13.520
Wait. wait. wait.
Wait. wait. <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

630
00:34:14.370 --> 00:34:16.470
Wait. No. wait. wait. wait.

631
00:34:16.480 --> 00:34:20.610
Wait! Yes! You're going back
to the Land of the Living!

632
00:34:20.610 --> 00:34:22.610
You know what? Maybe this
isn't such a good...

633
00:34:22.610 --> 00:34:25.350
No. no. <i>nino! Nino. nino.</i> I can help you.
You can help me.

634
00:34:25.350 --> 00:34:26.480
We can help each other.

635
00:34:26.490 --> 00:34:28.350
But most importantly.
you can help me.

636
00:34:28.350 --> 00:34:29.850
- Miguel!
- I'm Hector.

637
00:34:29.860 --> 00:34:31.410
- That's nice.
- <font color="#ff00ff">(YELPS)</font>

638
00:34:36.100 --> 00:34:37.750
<i>Esperame. chamaco!</i>

639
00:34:43.700 --> 00:34:45.570
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL GRUNTING)</font>

640
00:34:45.570 --> 00:34:48.140
<i>Ay.</i> he is going
to get himself killed.

641
00:34:48.140 --> 00:34:51.760
I need my spirit guide...
Pepita. <font color="#ff00ff">(WHISTLES)</font>

642
00:34:52.180 --> 00:34:54.500
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCREECHING)</font>

643
00:35:03.460 --> 00:35:05.530
Who has that petal
Miguel touched?

644
00:35:05.530 --> 00:35:08.640
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GROWLING)</font>
- Here. Nice alebrije.

645
00:35:08.700 --> 00:35:10.010
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

646
00:35:10.670 --> 00:35:12.920
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNIFFING)</font>

647
00:35:14.700 --> 00:35:16.520
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNARLING)</font>

648
00:35:20.140 --> 00:35:21.680
<font color="#ff00ff">(CLATTERS)</font>

649
00:35:21.680 --> 00:35:25.990
<i>Ay. ay.</i> hold still. Look up. <i>A ver. a ver.</i>
Look up. up. up.

650
00:35:26.280 --> 00:35:27.280
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNIFFING)</font>

651
00:35:27.280 --> 00:35:32.420
<i>Aqui arriba. eso...</i>
Eh. <i>la rayita.</i>

652
00:35:32.420 --> 00:35:35.000
Okay. Hey! Ta-da!

653
00:35:35.690 --> 00:35:37.540
Dead as a doorknob.

654
00:35:38.490 --> 00:35:41.600
So listen. Miguel.
this place runs on memories.

655
00:35:41.600 --> 00:35:42.830
When you're well remembered.

656
00:35:42.830 --> 00:35:44.700
people put up your photo
and you get to...

657
00:35:44.700 --> 00:35:46.300
cross the bridge
and visit the living

658
00:35:46.300 --> 00:35:48.770
on <i>Dia de Muertos.</i>
Unless you're me.

659
00:35:48.770 --> 00:35:50.570
You don't get
to cross over?

660
00:35:50.570 --> 00:35:51.840
No one's ever
put up my picture.

661
00:35:51.840 --> 00:35:53.620
But you can change that!

662
00:35:53.840 --> 00:35:55.610
<font color="#138ce9">MIGUEL:</font> This is you?

663
00:35:55.610 --> 00:35:57.250
Eh. <i>muy guapo.</i> eh?

664
00:35:57.250 --> 00:36:00.350
So. you get me
to my great-great-grandpa...

665
00:36:00.350 --> 00:36:03.250
then I put up your photo
when I get home?

666
00:36:03.250 --> 00:36:06.920
Such a smart boy! Yes!
Great idea. yes! One hiccup.

667
00:36:06.930 --> 00:36:08.860
De la Cruz is
a tough guy to get to

668
00:36:08.860 --> 00:36:10.660
and I need to
cross the bridge soon.

669
00:36:10.660 --> 00:36:11.660
Like. tonight.

670
00:36:11.660 --> 00:36:13.630
So. you got any other
family here. you know?

671
00:36:13.630 --> 00:36:15.770
Someone a bit more.
eh. accessible?

672
00:36:15.770 --> 00:36:17.600
Mmm... Nope.

673
00:36:17.600 --> 00:36:18.930
Don't yank my chain.
<i>chamaco.</i>

674
00:36:18.940 --> 00:36:20.540
You got to have
some other family.

675
00:36:20.540 --> 00:36:21.870
Only de la Cruz.

676
00:36:21.870 --> 00:36:23.910
If you can't help me.
I'll find him myself.

677
00:36:23.910 --> 00:36:25.340
<font color="#ff00ff">(MIGUEL WHISTLES)</font>

678
00:36:25.340 --> 00:36:27.780
Oh! Okay. Okay. kid.
Fine! Fine!

679
00:36:27.780 --> 00:36:29.660
I'll get you to your
great-great-grandpa.

680
00:36:31.350 --> 00:36:32.820
It's not gonna
be easy. you know?

681
00:36:32.820 --> 00:36:35.950
He's a busy man.
What are you doing?

682
00:36:35.960 --> 00:36:38.620
I'm walking like a skeleton.
Blending in.

683
00:36:38.620 --> 00:36:40.420
No. Skeletons
don't walk like that.

684
00:36:40.430 --> 00:36:44.490
- It's how you walk.
- No. I don't! Stop it!

685
00:36:44.500 --> 00:36:48.430
Whoa! Ernesto de la Cruz's
Sunrise Spectacular?

686
00:36:48.440 --> 00:36:50.230
- <i>Que padre!</i>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font>

687
00:36:50.240 --> 00:36:53.370
Every year your great-great-grandpa
puts on that dumb show...

688
00:36:53.370 --> 00:36:54.810
to mark the end
of <i>Dia de Muertos.</i>

689
00:36:54.810 --> 00:36:57.370
- And you can get us in!
- Um...

690
00:36:57.380 --> 00:36:59.640
Hey. you said you have
front row tickets!

691
00:36:59.650 --> 00:37:02.850
That... was a lie.
I apologize for that.

692
00:37:02.850 --> 00:37:05.020
Cool off. <i>chamaco.</i>
Come on. I'll get you to him.

693
00:37:05.020 --> 00:37:06.120
How?

694
00:37:06.120 --> 00:37:08.230
Because I happen to know
where he's rehearsing.

695
00:37:18.800 --> 00:37:22.980
<font color="#138ce9">DE LA CRUZ:</font> <i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Remember me
Don't let it make you cry </font><font color="#ffff00">♪</i></font>

696
00:37:24.270 --> 00:37:26.540
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font> You better have
my dress. Hector.

697
00:37:26.540 --> 00:37:27.920
<font color="#138ce9">HECTOR:</font> <i>Hola.</i> Ceci.

698
00:37:28.980 --> 00:37:30.920
<font color="#ff00ff">(HECTOR YELPS)</font>

699
00:37:32.580 --> 00:37:33.750
<font color="#ffff00">♪ </font><font color="#ffff00">♪</font>

700
00:37:33.750 --> 00:37:38.020
- <i>Hola.</i>
- Ceci. I lost the dress.

701
00:37:38.020 --> 00:37:39.690
<i>Ya lo sabia!</i>

702
00:37:39.690 --> 00:37:41.950
I got to dress
forty dancers by sunrise.

703
00:37:41.960 --> 00:37:45.820
Thanks to you. I'm one Frida
short of an opening number!

704
00:37:45.830 --> 00:37:49.910
Dante!
We shouldn't be in here.

705
00:37:55.970 --> 00:37:57.290
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

706
00:38:01.310 --> 00:38:03.160
- <font color="#ff00ff">(CHITTERING)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(BARKING)</font>

707
00:38:04.850 --> 00:38:07.160
No. no. Dante! <i>Ven aca!</i>

708
00:38:07.620 --> 00:38:09.030
<font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTS)</font>

709
00:38:15.990 --> 00:38:17.860
You! How did you
get in here?

710
00:38:17.860 --> 00:38:22.030
- I just followed my...
- Oh! The mighty Xolo dog!

711
00:38:22.030 --> 00:38:25.000
Guider of wandering spirits.

712
00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:28.040
And whose spirit
have you guided to me?

713
00:38:28.040 --> 00:38:30.400
I don't think
he's a spirit guide.

714
00:38:30.410 --> 00:38:31.410
Ah. ah. ah.

715
00:38:31.410 --> 00:38:34.480
The alebrijes of this world
can take many forms.

716
00:38:34.480 --> 00:38:37.800
They are as mysterious
as they are powerful.

717
00:38:39.350 --> 00:38:40.670
<font color="#ff00ff">(COUGHS)</font>

718
00:38:43.390 --> 00:38:47.240
Or maybe he's just a dog.
Come. I need your eyes.

719
00:38:48.490 --> 00:38:52.660
You are the audience.
Darkness.

720
00:38:52.660 --> 00:38:56.880
And from the darkness.
a giant papaya.

721
00:38:57.840 --> 00:39:00.840
Dancers emerge
from the papaya.

722
00:39:00.840 --> 00:39:04.910
and the dancers are all me.

723
00:39:04.910 --> 00:39:07.640
And they go to drink from
the milk of their mother.

724
00:39:07.650 --> 00:39:08.850
who is a cactus.

725
00:39:08.850 --> 00:39:10.580
But who is also me.

726
00:39:10.580 --> 00:39:14.900
And her milk is
not milk but tears.

727
00:39:15.860 --> 00:39:16.920
Is it too obvious?

728
00:39:16.920 --> 00:39:20.660
I think it's just
the right amount of obvious?

729
00:39:20.660 --> 00:39:24.060
It could use some music.
Oh. what if you did like...

730
00:39:24.060 --> 00:39:26.060
- <font color="#ff00ff">(SINGS TUNE)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(SNAPS FINGERS)</font>

731
00:39:26.060 --> 00:39:27.470
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL PLAYING TUNE)</font>

732
00:39:27.470 --> 00:39:28.930
Oh! And then it could go...

733
00:39:28.930 --> 00:39:31.540
<font color="#ff00ff">(SINGING TUNE)</font>

734
00:39:31.540 --> 00:39:34.540
<font color="#ff00ff">(PLAYING TUNE)</font>

735
00:39:34.540 --> 00:39:37.410
And what if
everything was on fire?

736
00:39:37.410 --> 00:39:39.610
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>
- Yes! Fire! Everywhere!

737
00:39:39.610 --> 00:39:43.820
Inspired! You have
the spirit of an artist.

738
00:39:43.820 --> 00:39:45.750
<font color="#ff00ff">(BAND PLAYING)</font>

739
00:39:45.750 --> 00:39:48.690
The dancers exit. The music
fades. the lights go out.

740
00:39:48.690 --> 00:39:52.020
And Ernesto de la Cruz
rises to the stage!

741
00:39:52.030 --> 00:39:53.340
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

742
00:39:55.830 --> 00:39:57.130
Huh?

743
00:39:57.130 --> 00:39:59.460
He does a couple of songs. the
sun rises. everyone cheers...

744
00:39:59.470 --> 00:40:02.000
Excuse me.
where's the real de la Cruz?

745
00:40:02.000 --> 00:40:04.100
Ernesto doesn't do
rehearsals!

746
00:40:04.100 --> 00:40:08.020
He's too busy hosting that fancy
party at the top of his tower.

747
00:40:10.180 --> 00:40:11.340
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

748
00:40:11.350 --> 00:40:13.650
<i>Chamaco.</i> you can't run off
on me like that.

749
00:40:13.650 --> 00:40:15.480
Stop pestering
the celebrities.

750
00:40:15.480 --> 00:40:17.650
You said my great-great-grandpa
would be here!

751
00:40:17.650 --> 00:40:20.520
He's halfway across town
throwing some big party.

752
00:40:20.520 --> 00:40:22.920
That bum. Who doesn't show up
to his own rehearsal?

753
00:40:22.930 --> 00:40:25.860
If you're such good friends.
how come he didn't invite you?

754
00:40:25.860 --> 00:40:28.730
He's your great-great-grandpa.
how come he didn't invite you?

755
00:40:28.730 --> 00:40:31.730
Hey. Gustavo! You know
anything about this party?

756
00:40:31.730 --> 00:40:33.170
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font>
It's the hot ticket!

757
00:40:33.170 --> 00:40:34.770
But if you're not
on the guest list.

758
00:40:34.770 --> 00:40:37.210
you're never
getting in. <i>Chorizo.</i>

759
00:40:37.210 --> 00:40:40.010
- Hey! It's <i>Chorizo! Choricito!</i>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

760
00:40:40.010 --> 00:40:41.640
A-ha. Very funny. guys.
Very funny.

761
00:40:41.640 --> 00:40:42.880
<i>Chorizo?</i>

762
00:40:42.880 --> 00:40:45.010
Oh. this guy's famous!

763
00:40:45.010 --> 00:40:47.150
Go on. go on.
Ask him how he died.

764
00:40:47.150 --> 00:40:48.780
I don't want
to talk about it.

765
00:40:48.790 --> 00:40:51.920
He choked on some <i>chorizo!</i>

766
00:40:51.920 --> 00:40:54.020
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

767
00:40:54.020 --> 00:40:55.760
I didn't choke. okay?

768
00:40:55.760 --> 00:40:57.760
I got food poisoning
which is a big difference.

769
00:40:57.760 --> 00:40:58.890
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

770
00:40:58.890 --> 00:41:00.530
This is why
I don't like musicians.

771
00:41:00.530 --> 00:41:02.160
Bunch of
self-important jerks.

772
00:41:02.170 --> 00:41:04.670
- Hey! I'm a musician!
- You are?

773
00:41:04.670 --> 00:41:07.500
If you really want
to get to Ernesto.

774
00:41:07.510 --> 00:41:08.900
there is that
music competition...

775
00:41:08.910 --> 00:41:10.570
at the Plaza de la Cruz.

776
00:41:10.580 --> 00:41:13.120
Winner gets
to play at his party.

777
00:41:14.080 --> 00:41:17.080
No. no. <i>Chamaco.</i>
you're <i>loco</i> if you think...

778
00:41:17.080 --> 00:41:19.520
I need to get my
great-great-grandfather's blessing!

779
00:41:19.520 --> 00:41:21.400
You know where
I can get a guitar?

780
00:41:21.990 --> 00:41:25.270
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font> I know a guy.

781
00:41:35.070 --> 00:41:36.800
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNIFFING)</font>

782
00:41:36.800 --> 00:41:39.940
Have you found him. Pepita?
Have you found our boy?

783
00:41:39.940 --> 00:41:41.140
<font color="#ff00ff">(BLOWS)</font>

784
00:41:41.140 --> 00:41:43.940
-<font color="#138ce9"> ROSITA:</font> A footprint!
- It's a Rivera boot.

785
00:41:43.940 --> 00:41:45.810
- Size seven!
- And a half.

786
00:41:45.810 --> 00:41:48.260
- Pronated.
- Miguel.

787
00:41:57.760 --> 00:41:59.690
<font color="#138ce9">HECTOR:</font> Why the heck would
you want to be a musician?

788
00:41:59.690 --> 00:42:01.560
<font color="#138ce9">MIGUEL:</font> My great-great-grandpa
was a musician!

789
00:42:01.560 --> 00:42:03.090
Who spent his life
performing like a monkey

790
00:42:03.100 --> 00:42:04.900
for complete strangers.

791
00:42:04.900 --> 00:42:07.300
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font> No thank you.
No! <i>Guacala!</i>

792
00:42:07.300 --> 00:42:09.170
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font>
What do you know?

793
00:42:09.170 --> 00:42:11.570
So. how far is
this guitar anyway?

794
00:42:11.570 --> 00:42:12.950
We're almost there.

795
00:42:13.270 --> 00:42:15.020
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

796
00:42:17.780 --> 00:42:19.360
Keep up. <i>chamaco.</i> Come on.

797
00:42:21.110 --> 00:42:22.960
<font color="#ff00ff">(HECTOR WHISTLES)</font>

798
00:42:24.850 --> 00:42:27.030
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

799
00:42:28.020 --> 00:42:32.730
- <font color="#138ce9">ALL:</font> Cousin Hector!
- Hey! These guys! Hey. <i>Tio!</i>

800
00:42:32.730 --> 00:42:33.860
<i>¿Que onda?</i>

801
00:42:33.860 --> 00:42:35.330
These people are
all your family?

802
00:42:35.330 --> 00:42:36.700
Uh...

803
00:42:36.700 --> 00:42:40.030
In a way. We're all the ones
with no photos or <i>ofrendas.</i>

804
00:42:40.030 --> 00:42:43.170
No family to go home to.
Nearly forgotten. you know?

805
00:42:43.170 --> 00:42:47.320
So. we all call each other
cousin. or <i>tio.</i> or whatever.

806
00:42:48.340 --> 00:42:51.740
- <font color="#ff00ff">(DANTE WHINES)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTING)</font>

807
00:42:51.750 --> 00:42:54.260
- Hector!
- <i>Tia</i> Chelo!

808
00:42:54.620 --> 00:42:56.050
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

809
00:42:56.050 --> 00:42:58.150
<i>Muchas gracias!</i>

810
00:42:58.150 --> 00:43:00.690
Hey! Save some for me!
Is Chicharron around?

811
00:43:00.690 --> 00:43:01.850
<font color="#138ce9">CHELO:</font> Eh. in the bungalow.

812
00:43:01.860 --> 00:43:04.360
I don't know if he's in
the mood for visitors.

813
00:43:04.360 --> 00:43:07.640
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font> Who doesn't like
a visit from Cousin Hector?

814
00:43:11.070 --> 00:43:12.950
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(CLATTERS)</font>

815
00:43:16.810 --> 00:43:18.670
<i>Buenas noches.</i> Chicharron!

816
00:43:18.670 --> 00:43:21.110
I don't want to see
your stupid face. Hector.

817
00:43:21.110 --> 00:43:23.180
Come on.
It's <i>Dia de Muertos.</i>

818
00:43:23.180 --> 00:43:24.780
I brought you
a little offering.

819
00:43:24.780 --> 00:43:26.850
- Get out of here.
- I would. Cheech.

820
00:43:26.850 --> 00:43:29.500
But the thing is.
me and my friend. Miguel...

821
00:43:30.650 --> 00:43:32.350
We really need
to borrow your guitar.

822
00:43:32.360 --> 00:43:33.920
- My guitar?
- Yes.

823
00:43:33.920 --> 00:43:36.220
My prized beloved guitar?

824
00:43:36.230 --> 00:43:38.060
I promise
we'll bring it right back.

825
00:43:38.060 --> 00:43:40.730
Like the time you promised
to bring back my van?

826
00:43:40.730 --> 00:43:42.200
- Uh...
- Or my mini-fridge?

827
00:43:42.200 --> 00:43:43.930
- Ah. you see...
- Or my good napkins?

828
00:43:43.940 --> 00:43:45.770
My lasso? My femur?

829
00:43:45.770 --> 00:43:47.000
Well. no.
not like those times.

830
00:43:47.000 --> 00:43:49.340
Where is my femur?
You... <font color="#ff00ff">(GROANING)</font>

831
00:43:49.340 --> 00:43:51.340
Whoa. whoa.

832
00:43:51.340 --> 00:43:55.260
- You okay. <i>amigo?</i>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font> I'm fading. Hector.

833
00:43:55.850 --> 00:43:58.280
I can feel it.

834
00:43:58.280 --> 00:44:01.470
I couldn't even play
that thing if I wanted to.

835
00:44:04.690 --> 00:44:07.220
You play me something.

836
00:44:07.230 --> 00:44:09.290
No. You know
I don't play anymore. Cheech.

837
00:44:09.300 --> 00:44:11.230
The guitar is for the kid.

838
00:44:11.230 --> 00:44:15.010
You want it.
you got to earn it.

839
00:44:16.400 --> 00:44:19.280
<i>Ay.</i> only for you. <i>amigo.</i>

840
00:44:20.370 --> 00:44:21.840
<font color="#ff00ff">(STRUMMING)</font>

841
00:44:21.840 --> 00:44:23.240
Any requests?

842
00:44:23.240 --> 00:44:27.330
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>
You know my favorite. Hector.

843
00:44:28.450 --> 00:44:30.430
<font color="#ff00ff">(PLAYING SOFT MUSIC)</font>

844
00:44:44.800 --> 00:44:48.510
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Well.
everyone knows Juanita</i></font>

845
00:44:49.470 --> 00:44:53.090
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Her eyes
each a different color</i></font>

